description: head() returns the first n rows.
head() returns the same type as the caller.
head() behavior mirrors df[:n] for positive n.
quote: This method returns the same rows as df[:n].
For negative values of n, this function returns all rows except the last n rows

description: Negative n returns all rows except the last |n| rows.
quote: For negative values of n, this function returns all rows except the last n rows, equivalent to df[:-n].

description: When n is larger than the number of rows, all rows are returned.
quote: If n is larger than the number of rows, this function returns all rows.
